      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "It's a very strange and unintuitive interface. The passed out hash will be null if `block.nNonce == std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()`. The nullness of that out-param is what is used to determine whether the outer while loop should increment the height or try again at the same height.",
