   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Thanks for the reviews @theStack and @Empact. I realize now that I've misread the new `GenerateBlock()` function and that the effective tri-state return means that the extranonce _can_ be incremented if we exit from `GenerateBlock()` with `block_hash` unset.\r\n\r\nI think it's very confusing that state is being passed around and shared between `generateBlocks()`, `GenerateBlock()`, and `IncrementExtraNonce()` (which is storing a `static` variable of the hash of the previous block). I think that could be clarified/cleaned up, but for now I'm just going to close this PR.",
      "created_at" : "2021-04-14T12:38:34Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/21533#issuecomment-819485464",
      "id" : 819485464,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/21533",
      "node_id" : "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDgxOTQ4NTQ2NA==",
      "performed_via_github_app" : null,
      "updated_at" : "2021-04-14T12:38:34Z",
      "url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/comments/819485464",
